      "content": "that sounds like a pretty strong stance. but some would say that ignoring the debt is just as much of a moral failure because it's essentially stealing from future generations who will have to pay it back. isn't it technically more \"irresponsible\" to leave the next generation with a massive bill just to avoid tough decisions today?",
